# CLAUDE.md — OpsAI

> This file is the persistent context for Claude Code sessions on the **OpsAI** project.
> It is project-specific. Do not apply conventions from this file to other projects (e.g., BidShield AI, trading dashboard).

-----

## Project Identity

**OpsAI** is an AI-powered business operations platform for small-to-mid-market businesses (contractors, restaurants, retail). It combines bookkeeping, AI receipt scanning, supply reorder intelligence, HR, project management, and KPI dashboards into a single adaptive platform.

- **Stage:** Active development
- **Owner:** Stephen
- **Hosting:** AWS
- **Repo structure:** Mono-repo

-----

## Tech Stack

|Layer             |Technology                                                                 |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Backend           |FastAPI (Python)                                                           |
|Frontend          |React (TypeScript)                                                         |
|Mobile            |React Native                                                               |
|Database          |PostgreSQL (RDS)                                                           |
|Auth              |AWS Cognito                                                                |
|Storage           |AWS S3                                                                     |
|Infra             |AWS (ECS / EC2 / RDS / S3 / Cognito)                                       |
|Integrations      |Merge.dev (HR, accounting, ERP connectors)                                 |
|Project Management|Plane (self-hosted or cloud)                                               |
|AI/ML             |Anthropic Claude API (receipt scanning, reorder intelligence, KPI insights)|
|Receipts/OCR      |AWS Textract                                                               |

-----

## Mono-Repo Structure

```
opsai/
├── backend/          # FastAPI app
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── api/      # Route handlers
│   │   ├── core/     # Config, auth, middleware
│   │   ├── models/   # SQLAlchemy models
│   │   ├── schemas/  # Pydantic schemas
│   │   └── services/ # Business logic layer
│   └── tests/
├── frontend/         # React (TypeScript) web app
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   ├── pages/
│   │   ├── hooks/
│   │   ├── store/    # State management
│   │   └── api/      # API client layer
│   └── public/
├── mobile/           # React Native app
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── screens/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   └── navigation/
├── infra/            # AWS CDK or Terraform configs
├── docs/             # Architecture decisions, API contracts
└── CLAUDE.md         # This file
```

-----

## Architecture Decisions

- **Mono-repo** — all services in one repo for easier cross-layer refactoring
- **FastAPI over Django** — lighter weight, async-native, better for AI service integration
- **Merge.dev for integrations** — unified API for third-party HR/accounting connectors; do not build direct integrations unless Merge doesn’t support the target
- **Plane for project management** — embedded via iframe or API, not rebuilt from scratch
- **Claude API for AI features** — receipt scanning, supply reorder suggestions, natural language KPI queries; always route AI calls through `backend/app/services/ai_service.py`
- **AWS Textract** — primary OCR for receipt ingestion; Claude handles extraction/structuring post-OCR
- **Tiered pricing model** — Starter / Growth / Scale; feature flags control tier access

-----

## Naming Conventions

- Python: `snake_case` for variables, functions, files; `PascalCase` for classes
- TypeScript/React: `camelCase` for variables/functions; `PascalCase` for components; `kebab-case` for file names
- API routes: RESTful, plural nouns — `/api/v1/receipts`, `/api/v1/suppliers`
- Database tables: `snake_case`, plural — `receipt_scans`, `reorder_events`
- Environment variables: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` — `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `MERGE_API_KEY`

-----

## Environment Variables (never hardcode)

```
# AWS
AWS_REGION
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
S3_BUCKET_NAME
COGNITO_USER_POOL_ID
COGNITO_CLIENT_ID

# Database
DATABASE_URL

# Third-party
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
MERGE_API_KEY
PLANE_API_KEY

# App
ENVIRONMENT=development|staging|production
```

-----

## Key Business Rules

- **Receipt scanning flow:** Upload to S3 → Textract OCR → Claude extraction → structured JSON → stored in `receipt_scans` table
- **Supply reorder logic:** Triggered when inventory drops below threshold; Claude generates reorder suggestions based on historical usage
- **Adaptive onboarding:** First-login flow adapts to business type (contractor vs. restaurant vs. retail); stored in `business_profile` table
- **KPI dashboards:** Configurable per business type; data pulled from internal DB + Merge.dev connectors
- **Feature flags:** Tier-gated features checked via `core/permissions.py` — never hardcode tier logic in route handlers

